---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import DisclaimerBanner from '../components/DisclaimerBanner.astro';
---

<Layout title="Provider Scope | Rabbia Ashraf & Associates">
  <SEO
    title="Understanding Provider Scope of Practice"
    description="Learn the difference between parent education, developmental guidance, psychological therapy, and assessment."
  />


  <main class="py-12 md:py-20 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6 text-center">Understanding Provider Scope</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-12 text-center">
        It is important to understand the different types of support available on this platform. Education and consultation are not the same as regulated therapy or diagnosis.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8">

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="bg-blue-50 border-b border-blue-100 p-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Guidance & Education Services</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Often available internationally</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <dl class="space-y-6">
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Parent Education</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Providing information, resources, and general strategies based on child development principles. It aims to empower parents with knowledge.</dd>
              </div>
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Parent Consultation</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">A collaborative process where a professional helps parents brainstorm solutions to specific challenges using the parent's knowledge of their child and the professional's expertise.</dd>
              </div>
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Developmental Guidance</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Information on what to expect at different stages of a child's development and how to support typical milestones.</dd>
              </div>
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Executive-Function Coaching</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Teaching strategies to help with organization, time management, task initiation, and working memory (often helpful for ADHD profiles).</dd>
              </div>
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">School Consultation</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Collaborating with educators to suggest accommodations, IEP goals, or classroom strategies to support a student's learning profile.</dd>
              </div>
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Behavior Support Planning</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Helping parents identify the function of a behavior and creating proactive routines and environmental adjustments to support the child.</dd>
              </div>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="bg-green-50 border-b border-green-100 p-6">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy">Regulated Clinical Services</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">Legally restricted to the provider's region of licensure</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <dl class="space-y-6">
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Psychological Therapy</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Treatment of mental health conditions using evidence-based clinical interventions. This is a regulated health service.</dd>
              </div>
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Psychological Assessment</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">The administration of standardized tests to evaluate cognitive, academic, or emotional functioning.</dd>
              </div>
              <div>
                <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Diagnosis</dt>
                <dd class="text-gray-700 text-sm">The formal identification of a mental health or neurodevelopmental condition (e.g., Autism, ADHD) according to diagnostic criteria (DSM-5 or ICD-11). Only qualified professionals licensed in the client's jurisdiction can provide a formal diagnosis.</dd>
              </div>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-2">Emergency Care</h2>
          <p class="text-red-700 text-sm">
            This platform is not suitable for emergencies, self-harm risk, abuse crisis, medical emergencies, or immediate safety concerns. In urgent situations, contact local emergency services, the nearest hospital, or a local licensed mental health professional.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

</Layout>
